{"key":"post-9016560","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>9016560</id>\n<content>You don't want the cake to wick up water from the perlite. Good flushes depend on a cycle of moisture content.&amp;nbsp; You want your cakes to dry out slightly, and then replace that moisture.&amp;nbsp; This is one of the main pinning triggers.&amp;nbsp; If you set it on the perlite, moisture content remains stable and performance suffers compared to what it would be if you did it correctly.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>9016885</next>\n<prev>9016007</prev>\n<first>8997665</first>\n<last>9016889</last>\n<when>1222928429</when>\n<utime>10/02/08 09:20 AM</utime>\n</post>"}